Yobe State Governor and Chairman APC Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, Mai Mala Buni has been inoculated against COVID-19 The governor was administered the AstraZeneca vaccine by his physician Dr. Mohammed Salim Umar, assisted by the State Commissioner of Health and Human Services, Dr. Mohammed Lawan Gana on Sunday.  Also vaccinated were the State Deputy Governor, Idi Barde Gubana; Secretary to the State Government, Baba Malam Wali; Commissioner of Humanitarian Affairs, Dr. Garba Iliya; Chief of State, Abdullahi Yusuf as well as other Personal Aids to the governor. The vaccination against COVID-19 in the state also marks the official launching of the exercise with Gov. Buni urging people in the state to go out and take the jab. More political appointees in the state are expected to answer the clarion call. DAILY POST gathered that after the Yobe State government took delivery of 65, 610 doses of COVID-19 vaccine, it immediately embarked on the vaccinating of health workers in line with the presidential task forcesâ€™ recommendation.